      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The <sup>1</sup>H NMR spectrum shown is that of 3-methyl-3-buten-1-ol. Assign all the observed resonance peaks to specific protons, and account for the splitting patterns.</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdklWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--f47828d8477bd9babb98a262353cd792d7f13dab/OChem_17_EC_039.jpg\" alt=\"H N M R spectrum with shifts at 1.76 (singlet), 2.13 (singlet), 2.30 (triplet), 3.72 (triplet), 4.79 (singlet), 4.85 (singlet). Relative areas are 3, 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, respectively.\">",
